==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ultramontanism
<hw>Ul`tra*mon"ta*nism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>ultramontanisme</ets>.]</ety> <def>The principles of those within
the Roman Catholic Church who maintain extreme views favoring the pope's
supremacy; -- so used by those living north of the Alps in reference to
the Italians; -- rarely used in an opposite sense, as referring to the
views of those living north of the Alps and opposed to the papal claims.
Cf. <er>Gallicanism</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ultramontanist</ent>⟦br⟧
